#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
validate-schema — Validate structured data files against schema definitions.

Two operating modes:
  1. `--all` or `--niche N-XXX` (Batch mode)
     Scans one or all niche directories, infers schemas from filenames, and
     validates every YAML file (including trace-map.yaml).  JSON output.
  2. `DATA_TYPE FILE_PATH` (Single-file mode, backward-compatible)
     Validates one file against a named schema.

Google SRE pattern: validates data at ingestion time, not mid-canvas.
Catches schema violations early — prevents bad data from propagating
into canvas authoring and contaminating downstream analysis.

Usage (batch mode):
    ./validate-schema --all [--verbose]
    ./validate-schema --niche N-XXX [--verbose]

Usage (single-file mode):
    ./validate-schema DATA_TYPE FILE_PATH [--schema-dir PATH] [--dry-run]

DATA_TYPE is one of: competitor-profile, review-corpus, market-sizing,
                     canvas-frontmatter

Exit codes:
    0  PASS                 All checks passed, no issues.
    1  FAIL                 Blocking violations found.
    2  PASS_WITH_WARNINGS   Non-blocking issues found.
    3  INTERNAL_ERROR       Script bug, corrupted schema/data YAML, or
                            missing dependency. Escalate to Wesley.
    4  INVALID_INPUT        Invalid arguments, unknown data type, or file
                            not found.

Output: Structured JSON to stdout. Human-readable logs to stderr.
"""

